Made sprite for zig-zaggers,I also borrowed a shell script from another of my repositories.

Changed Zig-Zagger's characteristics (e.g. horizontal speed),I realize that it's odd that I only switch the current waypoint based on,time rather than on the waypoint's being reached,but since there's only,one Zig-Zagger,I don't think fixing the issue is worth the time.
Two waypoints for zig zaggers are set and alternated correctly
Original waypoint is randomly set for WaypointEnemy instances,Thus,WaypointEnemies won't always go left at the very beginning of the,level.

Made class ZigZag for enemies that zig-zag (i.e. go back and forth),I had to make some adjustments to WaypointEnemy to make it more general,,since not every WaypointEnemy (e.g. the ZigZag) cares about the player's,position. I used the asteroid sprite to test the new enemy.

Changed some private identifiers in PlayerSpacecraft for consistency,That is,I replaced "horizontal" and "vertical" with "X" and "Y",,respectively,where appropriate,since I'd been using "X" and "Y" in some,of the other classes. Also,I know this doens't relate to this feature,branch,but I thought I'd deal with it now anyway.

Started revising the class hierarchy,For this commit,I created a class called WaypointEnemy that IS-A,EnemyEntity. To test this new class,I changed class Hunter so that it,IS-A WaypointEnemy. My plan is for the proposed enemies that need,waypoints (e.g. the ambusher) to extend WaypointEnemy and for the ones,that don't to inherit directly from EnemyEntity. I'm not sure whether to,make WaypointEnemy abstract,though. Part of me thinks it makes sense,but,part of me thinks it's an odd move,even though EnemyEntity is abstract. I,don't think this decision will be consequential,though.

Updated todo list,I can't think of a good way to try to release the MediaPlayer instance if,an exception is thrown. I think such an effort could lead to more problems,(e.g. releasing the instance twice). Furthermore,I thought of many ideas,for enemies after doing some research into the unique aspects of each,ghost in Pac-Man.
Completed distance is output if user beats level
Remaining distance is output if user loses

Each protagonist spacecraft has different speed,I didn't pick good speeds yet. Nor did I just the levels appropriately.,Furthermore,note that these changes involved both vertical and horizontal,speeds. I hope to improve the speeds and levels before the next release.
Can choose between three spacecrafts of different sizes and shapes,I managed to adjust the unit tests appropriately,so they were useful in,making these changes.

Player can choose between hero spacecraft and asteroid,Yup,he can play as an asteroid. That option will not be in the final app,(unless I decide to do some silly easter eggs). Furthermore,the HERO,value of Entity.Type has been removed.

Added methods to send DB over I/O stream,Added two methods to Library class that can be used for sending the,library over a connection between devices. Each table in the library is,taken one by one and each of its rows' values along with column names,are put into a JSON object which is then sent over the provided,OutputStream. At the receiving end,the same JSON object is retrieved,from the InputStream and decoded back into a row and inserted into the,same table in the database. Still need to implement sending album art.,I've tried to write the methods as generalized as possible so that,changing columns or adding new tables in the future won't require,updating these methods.,Changes:,Table:,  -Added a constructor to get table name. This can be used by Library,  when accessing a table' name through abstract class 'Table' reference,  -added method to get a cursor of all columns and rows,  -added method to insert values into a new row in table,SongTable,AlbumTable,ArtistTable:,  -calls Table's new constructor,  -uses insertValues(),Library:,  -Forgot to set querySongs() ordering back to song title. (was set to,  album name for testing in previous commit),  -Added two methods for sending/receiving the entire library database,  over input/output streams as JSON objects

Reintroduced library with better implementation,removed splash gif,Decided to reintroduce the library database to try and see if it makes,transferring local database to remote devices easier. Content,provider is used only to obtain song,album and artist info and store,them into local tables in the library database. Required cursors are,queried from these tables. Allows querying between multiple tables which,the MediaStore could not do,and should hopefully make sending library,to other devices a simple process of sending columns of these tables.,This time,libraryDb uses transactions for loading the library making it,twice as fast as past Library DB implementation. Startup initialization,of database takes around 3 seconds on my device.,Removed album art path caching since its stored in the Library DB now.,Removed the splash screen Gif. It was funny while it lasted and slowed,down startup slightly.,Changes:,SplashActivity:,  -Removed splash animation. The joke's run on long enough. R.I.P.,  Eldorado breakdown,Library:,  -Changed functionality. Now an instantiable class used for editing or,  obtaining the library database.,  -Removed album art database,New Classes:,Table:,  -An abstract class for any table to be added to the database. Contains,  required methods used by Library so that future tables can be added,  without much changes required,SongTable,AlbumTable,ArtistTable:,  -Extensions of Table for holding Media,Album,Artist information from,  ContentResolver

ArticleActivity: Start of code to load the SpannableStrings,Instead of a WebView the ArticleActivity now just creates a,LinearLayout with a TextView for each of the strings from the binary,dump of the article. The spans are currently skipped over instead of,being applied to the string.

pdb-db: Write out a binary file containing the sections of each article,Instead of dumping out the XML and getting the app to do process it,,the plan is now to write out a binary file with a list of,SpannableStrings for the app to display directly. This changes prevodb,to start building the array of strings. The XML document is now parsed,using a PdbDoc instead of trying to parse the data directly from,Expat. This makes the code a lot easier to maintain because it doesn't,have to manage a separate stack for the state and certain branches of,the tree can be handled multiple times.,Although the framework is setup to add spans to the strings all of the,strings are currently just output directly with no spans.,This patch breaks the translation indices and the marks for all of the,sections are zero. These will be fixed in later patches.
prevodb: Add a small unit test to check PdbDoc,This checks loading all of the XML files from a ReVo zip file and,verifies the integrity of the generated PdbDoc.

prevodb: Add an object to represent a mini DOM tree of an XML file,This adds a PdbDoc struct which represents a tree of an XML file. The,DOM is build up using a PdbXmlParser. The theory is that it will be a,lot simpler to build the articles from a DOM model than trying to use,SAX.
pdb-revo: Initialise in_list,Valgrind was picking this up as uninitialised data.
pdb-db: Fix the terminator for pdb_try_mkdir,error was being passed at the end instead of passing the NULL,terminator.
pdb-db: Don't forget to free the PdbDbArticle structs

pdb-revo: Change API to directly pull data instead of a callback,Instead of having a single function to read a file from the zip file,with a callback whenever data is encountered,there is now a struct to,represent an open file and the caller and directly call a function to,read the next chunk of data.

AppIntro2 6.0 permissions tweaks. Made second activity for example that uses AppIntro2.

[WIP] added semi-support for Android 6.0 permissions that is talked about in #84. Currently very buggy and not ready for production.,Testing has only been done with AppIntro and not AppIntro2.,Two new methods: slideSelected() and askForPermissions().,slideSelected() gets the current slide and returns it as an int.,askForPermission() takes a String array (String[]) and then goes on to request permission. See example app for how to actually request permissions for each slide. The process is tricky because the Android code doesn't have support for single permissions. That means you must pass a String[] rather than just a String if you're using one permission. The array only has one item at position 0 which would deem it worthless,however,the Android team didn't provide support for passing strings to their methods.,Bugs:,1. The request dialog pops up as the Next button is pressed rather than after. Desired result: slide talks about permission,the user presses next,and then a permission is show WITHOUT going to the next slide. After the user chooses allow or deny,he's taken to the next slide regardless of his previous answer.,2. Currently,only onNextPressed works. I tried doing an onPageScrolled but that caused a permission request to pop up for every inch (or whatever measurement scrolling is) that the page was scrolled. This obviously is not desired.,More time and testing will go into this,but I wanted to get the basic concept out there so people get a sense of progress.

All devices notified when a client leaves the group,SDK 25 support.,If a client leaves the group,no longer is the group owner the only,device that becomes aware of it. Now,all devices in the group are,notified of the leaving member and update perform required steps to,handle the client.,Changes:,NetworkService:,  -Renamed the binder class to NetworkServiceBinder to be more,  specific than "LocalBinder".,  -In RequestHandler,renamed the device address variable to,  senderDeviceAddress. Can't believe it took me this long to realize it's,  the address of the "sender" not the "receiver",  -There are now two methods of detecting a client that leaves.,Cm_message: 1. If disconnecting from the group in the app itself,the device sends,Cm_message: a notification that it's leaving to all other devices. They receive and,Cm_message: process this.,Cm_message: 2. In case the 1st one fails,like if the device disconnects from the,Cm_message: group manually instead of from inside the app,the,Cm_message: WifiP2pBroadcastReciever of the group owner will get the,Cm_message: notification. The owner then sends a notification to all other group,Cm_message: members of the client that left. This doesn't always work and isn't,Cm_message: always fast. So the 1st method is more reliable.,ShareGroup:,  -onOwnerDisconnected() action is executed on main thread to avoid,  UI exceptions from a separate thread.,  -The p2pBroadcastReceiver could possible call onMemberLeft after,  the member has already left,so a check for null pointer is uses for,  currentGroup.groupMembers.,build.gradle:,  -updated to compile for latest android version.
